obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (36407)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36407&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called "The Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy Baronetcy Act, 1915," and`
  line
  line `(2) Commencement.--It shall come into force at once.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (36408)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Repeal of Act XX of 1860.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36408&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `The said Act No. 20 of 1860 is hereby repealed, and the said`
  line `Promissory Notes of the Government of India, of the nominal value of rupees twenty-two lakhs, fifty-four`
  line `thousand and four hundred, shall henceforth cease to be vested in the Corporation created and constituted`
  line `by the said Act No. XX of 1860, and the Mansion House and other hereditaments, called Mazagon Castle,`
  line `situate in the Island of Bombay, with their rights, members and appurtenances, of which the said First`
  line `Baronet was seized to him and his heirs, shall, by force of this Act, from and immediately after the`
  line `passing of this Act, either as to the whole or, as the case may be, as to such parts thereof as shall not have`
  line `been sold, transferred, and conveyed under the powers conferred by section 10, stand limited, until such`
  line `time as the same shall have been sold, transferred, and conveyed under the powers conferred by the said`
  line `section 10, to the uses following (that is to say): to the use of the present, that is to say, the Fifth Baronet,`
  line `for and during the term of his natural life, and from and immediately after his decease, to the use of the`
  line `heirs male of the body of Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, First Baronet, who may succeed to the title of Baronet`
  line `conferred by the said Letters Patent as aforesaid, but as to each one of the said heirs male to the use of`
  line `such heir male during the term of his natural life only, and, upon failure and default of heirs male of the`
  line `body of the said Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, First Baronet, to whom the said tile and dignity of Baronet may descend as aforesaid to the use of the heirs, and assigns for ever of the said Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, the`
  line `Second Baronet, which ultimate remainder or reversion it shall be lawful for the heirs and assigns of the`
  line `said Second Baronet, at any time or times during the continuance of the said title and dignity of Baronet`
  line `and until there shall be such a failure of heirs male of the body of the said First Baronet as aforesaid, to`
  line `grant, convey, devise, and dispose of by Deed or Will, or by any other assurance or assurances by which`
  line `such an estate in remainder or reversion is capable by law of being conveyed or disposed of.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (36437)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `The Commissioner for the Northern Division, the Accountant - General, and the Collector of Bombay to be a Corporation for execution of the Trusts of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36437&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner for the time`
  line `being for the Northern Division of the Presidency of Bombay, the Accountant-General for the time being`
  line `of Bombay, and the Collector for the time being of Bombay, and the holders for the time being of those`
  line `offices respectively, and likewise the holder or holders for the time being of any one or more office or`
  line `offices which may hereafter be substituted by the Governor in Council of Bombay for any one or more of`
  line `the first mentioned offices, shall be, and they are hereby, created a Corporation with perpetual succession`
  line `and a common Seal under the style and title of "Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy Baronet's Trustees," and the said`
  line `Corporation so hereby created (hereinafter styled "the Corporation") are hereby constituted, as such`
  line `Corporation, the Trustees for executing the powers and purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (36410)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Present Baronet to continue to bear, and all future Baronet to take, names of First Baronet.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36410&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The present Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, Fifth Baronet, shall continue to be called by the name of`
  line `"Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy," and all other the heirs male of the body of Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, First Baronet,`
  line `to whom the said title and dignity shall descend, pursuant to the limitation of the Letters Patent whereby`
  line `the said dignity was granted, shall take upon themselves respectively the name of "Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy,"`
  line `in lieu and in the place of any other name or names whatsoever ; and the present Baronet, and all such`
  line `other heirs male of the said Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, First Baronet, severally and successively shall be`
  line `called by the name of "Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy," and by that name shall name, style, and write themselves,`
  line `respectively, upon all occasions whatsoever.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (36411)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Government Promissory Notes of a certain nominal value vested in Trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36411&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line Immediately
  line `from and after the passing of this Act, the said Promissory Notes of the Government of India, of the`
  line `nominal value of rupees twenty-two lakhs, fifty-four thousand and four hundred, shall vest in the`
  line `Corporation who shall hold the same upon the trusts, and for the purposes, and with the powers,`
  line `hereinafter expressed of and concerning the same, that is to say:`
  line
  line `(a) On trust to re-invest if paid off.Upon trust, if the same or any part thereof should be`
  line `discharged by the Government of India, to invest the sum or sums paid by the Government of India,`
  line `in discharge of the same or any part thereof, in or upon any stocks, funds, or securities in which they`
  line `are by the provisions of this Act hereinafter authorised to invest the same, and in like manner, as often`
  line `as the same shall become necessary, to alter, vary and change such stocks, funds, and securities for`
  line `others of the same or a like nature;`
  line
  line `(b) and to pay income to present Baronet for his life. and upon further trust, from time to`
  line `time, to pay and apply the dividends, interest, and annual income of the said stocks, funds, and`
  line `securities unto and for the benefit of the present Baronet, that is to say, Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, Fifth`
  line `Baronet, during his natural life ;`
  line
  line `(c) and after death of present Baronet to pay income to Baronet for time being.and upon`
  line `further trust, from and immediately after the decease of the said Sir Jamsetjee Jajeebhoy Fifth`
  line `Baronet, to pay and apply the said dividends, interest, and annual income unto and for the benefit of`
  line `the person who, as heir male of the body of the said Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, First Baronet, shall, for`
  line `the time being, have succeeded to, and be in the enjoyment of, the title of Baronet conferred by the`
  line `said Letters Patent as aforesaid, notwithstanding any rule of Law or Equity to the contrary ;`
  line
  line `(d) with ultimate trust for Second Baronet his executors, administrators and assigute.and`
  line `upon further trust, upon failure and in default of heirs male of the body of the said Sir Jamsetjee`
  line `Jejeebhoy, First Baronet, to whom the said title and dignity of Baronet may descend, to hold the`
  line `corpus and also the income of the said Government Promissory Notes, stocks, funds, and securities`
  line `for the heirs and assigns forever of Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, the Second Baronet, which ultimate remainder or reversion it shall be lawful for the heirs and assigns of Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, the`
  line `Second Baronet, at any time or times during the continuance of the said title and dignity of Baronet,`
  line `and until there shall be a failure of heirs male of the body of the said First Baronet as aforesaid, to`
  line `assign, transfer, bequeath and dispose of by Deed or Will or other assurance or assurances.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (36412)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Powers of investment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36412&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation shall have power to invest the funds, which are subject`
  line `to the trusts of the Settlement effected by this Act, on the following securities and on no others:—`
  line
  line `(a) in Promissory Notes, debentures, stock or other securities of the Government of India, or of`
  line `the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland;`
  line
  line `(b) in bonds, debentures or annuities charged by the Imperial Parliament, or by an Act of`
  line `Legislative Council of the Governor General of India, on the revenues of India;`
  line
  line `(c) in stock or debentures of or shares in Railway or other Companies, the interest whereon shall`
  line `have been guaranteed by the Secretary of State for India in Council;`
  line
  line `(d) in debentures or other securities for moneys issued by, or on, behalf of, any municipal body`
  line `under the authority of any Act of a Legislature established in British India, or debentures issued by`
  line `the Trustees for the Improvement of the City of Bombay under the City of Bombay Improvement,`
  line `Act, 1898 (Bombay Act 4 of 1898), or debentures issued by the Trustees of the Port of Bombay under`
  line `the Bombay Port Trust Act, 1879 (Bombay Act 6 of 1879), or debentures issued by the Trustees of`
  line `the Port of Karachi under the Local Authorities Loans Act, 1914 (Act 9 of 1914), or other law for the`
  line `time being in force, or debentures issued by the Commissioners for the Port of Rangoon under the`
  line `Local Authorities Loans Act, 1914 ( Act 9 of 1914), or the Rangoon Port Act, 1905 (Baronet Act 4 of`
  line `1905).`
  line
  line `(e) on any other security expressly authorised by any rule which the High Court of Judicature at`
  line `Bombay may, from time to time, prescribe as an investment for trust property consisting of money.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (36413)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Prohibition against varying investments without consent of person entitled to income.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36413&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Corporation shall not vary any investment of the funds, subject to the Settlement effected by this Act,`
  line `without the consent in writing of the person for the time being entitled to the income of the said Funds.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (36414)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to Baronet for the time being to purchase land to erect a Mansion House thereon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36414&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The person for the time being entitled to, and in the enjoyment of, the title of Baronet conferred by the`
  line `said Letters Patent, shall have power, with the written, approval of the Corporation,—`
  line
  line `(a) and to purchase land with a house thereon, and to pull the house down, and erect`
  line `another, or to enlarge, alter or add to house thereon.—to purchase land in any part of the Island of`
  line `Bombay for the purpose of erecting there on a Mansion House and all necessary or suitable accessory`
  line `buildings, and to erect thereon such Mansion House and accessory buildings;`
  line
  line `(b) to purchase land in any part of the Island of Bombay with a dwelling house standing thereon,`
  line `and either to pull down the said dwelling house and any other building which may be upon the land,`
  line `and to erect upon the said land, in lieu thereof, a Mansion House, with all necessary or suitable`
  line `accessory buildings, or to enlarge alter, or add to the building or buildings which may be upon the`
  line `land, when purchased, so as to convert the same into a Mansion House, with all necessary or suitable`
  line `accessory buildings.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (36415)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to trustees to sell securities to produce funds to pay for land, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36415&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation`
  line `shall have power to sell a sufficient portion of the securities upon which the funds, which are subject to`
  line `the Settlement effected by this Act, shall for the time being be invested to produce the sum which shall be`
  line `required for the purpose of paying for any land which may be purchesed by the person for the time being`
  line `entitled to, and in the enjoyment of, the title of Baronet conferred by the said Letters Patent under the`
  line `powers conferred by section 8, and for erecting thereon a Mansion House, with the necessary or suitable`
  line `accessory buildings, or for paying for the purchase of any land with a house or other building stading`
  line `thereon which may be purchased under the powers conferred as aforesaid, and for pulling down the said`
  line `buildings, and erecting a Mansion House, with the necessary or suitable accessory buildings, in liue thereof or for altering and adding to such buildings for the purpose of converting the same into a Mansion`
  line `House, with the necessary or sutable accessary buildings, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Proviso that total sum raised shall not exceed Rs. 2,25,000.—Provided that the total sum raised by`
  line `the Corporation under the power conferred upon them by this section for the sale of the said securities`
  line `above-mentioned shall not exceed two lakhs and twenty five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (36416)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power to Baronet for the time being to sell Mazngon Castle.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36416&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The person for the time being`
  line `entitled to, and in the enjoyment of, the title of Baronet conferred by the said Letters Patent, shall have`
  line `power, with the written consent and approval of the Corporation, to sell, transfer, and convey freed and`
  line `discharged from all uses and trusts created by this Act, the said Mansion House and other hereditaments,`
  line `called Mazagon Castle, situate in the Island of Bombay, with their rights, members and appurtenances,`
  line `and either in one parcel or in several parcels, and either at one time or from time to time, upon condition`
  line `that the proceeds of sale thereof shall be paid by the purchaser thereof direct to the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (36438)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to Trustees to apply proceeds of sale Mazagon Castle, not exceeding Rs. 2,75,000 in paying for land purchased and for erecting Mansion House th ere on, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36438&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The person for the time`
  line `being entitle to, and in the enjoyment of, the title of Baronet, conferred by the said Letters Patent may,`
  line `from time to time, request the Corporation, in writing, to pay, out of the proceeds of sale of the said`
  line `Mansion House and other hereditaments, called Mazagon Castle, if and when sold, the purchase money of`
  line `any land which may be purchased by the person for the time being entitled to, and in the enjoyment of,`
  line `the said title of Baronet, under the powers conferred by section 8; and all costs, charges, and expenses of,`
  line `and incidental to the purchase and acquisition of the same, and of the conveyance, and assurance of the`
  line `same to the Corporation, and also to pay all costs and expenses of, and incidental to the erection thereon`
  line `of, a Mansion House, with the necessary or suitable accessory buildings, and to pay the purchase money`
  line `of any land, with a house, or other building, standing thereon, which may be purchased by the person for`
  line `the time being entitled to, and in the enjoyment of, the said title of Baronet, under the powers conferred`
  line `by this Act, and all costs, charges and expenses of, and incidental to, the purchase and acquisition of the`
  line `same, and of the conveyance, and assurance of the same to the Corporation, and also to pay all costs, and`
  line `expenses of, and incidental to the pulling down of the said buildings, or any of them and of erecting a`
  line `Mansion House, with the necessary of suitable accessory buildings, in lieu thereof, or of altering, and`
  line `adding to, such buildings, for the purpose of converting the some into a Mansion House, with the`
  line `necessary or suitable accessory buildings, as the case may be, and the Corporation shall, upon such`
  line `request being made as aforesaid, make such payments out of the proceeds of sale of the said Mansion`
  line `House and other hereditaments called Mazagon Castle:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total sum expended by the Corporation, under the powers conferred by this section,`
  line `out of the proceeds of sale of the said Mansion House and other hereditaments, called Mazagon Castle,`
  line `shall not exceed the sum of two lakhs and seventy-five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (36418)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Settlement of Mansion House, etc., in support of Baronetcy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36418&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `All lands and buildings which`
  line `may be purchased by the person for the time being entitled to, and in the enjoyment of, the title of`
  line `Baronet under the said Letters Patent under the powers conferred by section 8, with their rights, members,`
  line `and appurtenances shall be conveyed to the Corporation, and the Corporation shall hold the same, and`
  line `also all buildings which may be erected thereon under the powers conferred by section 8, upon trust for`
  line `Sir, Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, Fifth Baronet, for and during the term of his natural life, and from and`
  line `immediately after his decease, upon trust for the heirs male of the body of Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, First`
  line `Baronet, who may succeed to the title of Baronet conferred by the said Letters Patent, but as to each one`
  line `of the said heirs male upon trust for such heir male during the term of his natural life only, and, upon`
  line `failure and default of heirs male of the body of the said Sir Jamstjee Jejeebhoy, First Baronet, to whom`
  line `the said title and dignity of Baronet, may descend as aforesaid, upon trust for the heirs and assigns of Sir`
  line `Jamsejee Jejeebhoy, the Second Baronet, which ultimate remainder or reversion it shall be lawful for the`
  line `heirs and assigns of the said Second Baronet at any time or times during the continuance of the said title`
  line `and dignity of Baronet, and until there shall be such failure of heirs male of the body of the said First`
  line `Baronet to grant, convey, devise and dispose of by Deed or Will, or by any other assurance or assurances`
  line `by which such an estate in remainder or reversion is capable by law of being conveyed or disposed of.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (36439)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Saving of rights of persons interested in reversion or remainder in Mazagon Castle on sale thereof`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36439&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Any person or persons who shall have lawfully derived from the said Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy,`
  line `Second Baronet, any interest in remainder or reversion in the said Mansion House and other`
  line `hereditaments, called Mazagon Castle, contingent upon such failure and default of heirs male of the body`
  line `of Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, First Baronet, shall, upon such failure and default of heirs male of the body of`
  line `Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, First Baronet, in the event of the said Mansion House and other hereditaments,`
  line `called Mazagon Castle, having been sold in pursuance of the power in that behalf conferred by section 10`
  line `be deemed to have a corresponding interest in the funds for the time being subject to the trusts of the`
  line `Settlement effected by this Act to the extent of the amount of the proceeds of sale of the said Mansion`
  line `House and other hereditaments, called Mazagon Castle, paid to the said Corporation in pursuance of`
  line `section 10.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (36440)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Declaration of Trusts as to surplus proceeds of sale of Mazagon Castle over and above the sum of Rs. 2,75,000.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36440&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation shall hold so much, if any of the proceeds of sale of the said`
  line `Mansion House and other hereditaments, called Mazagon Castle, if and when sold, as shall exceed the`
  line `sum of two lakhs and seventy-five thousand rupees, upon trust, to invest the same upon one or more of`
  line `the investments authorised by section 6, and shall hold the said investments, upon the same trusts, and for`
  line `the same ends, intents and purposes, and with the same powers, as are, by this Act, declared of and`
  line `concerning the funds which are subject to the Settlement effected by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (36441)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power to Trustees to invest the surplus annual interest and income of the Trust Fund and p remises during the minority of any Baronet etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36441&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation during the minority of any person`
  line `for the time being entitled to, and in the enjoyment of, the title of Baronet under the limitations of the said`
  line `Letters Patent, shall pay and apply for and towards the maintenance, education, and benefit of such`
  line `Baronet, in each and every year during his minority so much only of the annual interest, dividends and`
  line `income of the said Trust Funds and premises as the Corporation shall, in their discretion, think proper;`
  line `and shall, from time to time, invest the residue of the said annual dividends, interest, and income of the`
  line `said Trust Funds and premises in and upon some one or more of the investments authorised by this Act`
  line `for the investment of the said Trust Funds; and shall, upon such Baronet attaining his majority, pay over,`
  line `transfer, and assign to him, or as he shall direct and for his own absolute benefit, the said investments and`
  line `all accumulations thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (36422)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Provision in case of refusal or discontinuance of names of First Baronet.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36422&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Provided always`
  line `that in case any person who, for the time being, shall be the heir male of the body of the said First Baronet`
  line `to whom the said title of Baronet shall have descended, shall for the space of one whole year after he`
  line `shall, by virtue of this Act, become entitled to the dividends, interest, and income of the said stocks,`
  line `funds, and securities or to the possession or receipts of the rents and profits of the said hereditaments; or,`
  line `being then under age, shall for the space of one whole year after he shall attain the age of twenty-one`
  line `years, refuse or neglect to use the names of "Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy" as hereinbefore enacted; or in case any`
  line `such person having so used those name, shall, for the space of six calendar months consecutively during`
  line `his natural life, discontinue so to use such names, then, in any or either of the said cases, the estate or`
  line `interest of the person who shall so refuse or neglect to use, or, having used, shall so discontinue to use,`
  line `the said names of "Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy" shall, during the remainder of his respective natural life, be`
  line `suspended; and that during any and every such suspension, the dividends, interest, and income of the said`
  line `stocks, funds and securities, and the possession and actual occupation, and also the rents and profits of the`
  line `said hereditaments, shall devolve and belong to the person who as heir male of the body of the First`
  line `Baronet, would have succeeded to, and been in the enjoyment of, the title of Baronet conferred by the said`
  line `Letters Patent, in case the persons so refusing or neglecting to use, or discontinuing to use, the said names`
  line `of "Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy" had departed this life; but if there should be no such heir male, then to the`
  line `person or persons who would be entitled to the same in case there had then been a total failure of issue`
  line `male of the First Baronet entitled to the said dignity of Baronet.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (36423)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Baronet in possession may jointure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36423&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, Fifth`
  line `Baronet, and for any person upon whom the said title of Baronet shall, from time to time, descend when`
  line `in the actual enjoyment of the said title, and who shall not refuse, neglect, or discontinue to use, for the`
  line `respective periods hereinbefore in that behalf mentioned, the said names of "Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy" as`
  line `hereinbefore enacted, either before or after his marriage with any woman or women by any Deed or Deeds, writing or writings, with or without power of revocation, to be by him sealed and delivered in the`
  line `presence of two or more credible witnesses (but subject and without prejudice to any annuity or annuities,`
  line `if any, which shall be then subsisting and payable by virtue of any appointment made under and in`
  line `pursuance of this present power), to limit and appoint unto any woman or women whom he shall marry,`
  line `for her or their life or lives, and for her or their jointure, or jointures, in bar of dower or other legal or`
  line `customary rights, any annuity or yearly sum not exceeding the sum of rupees ten thousand, clear of all`
  line `taxes, charges and deductions whatsoever, to commence and take effect immediately after the decease of`
  line `the person limiting or appointing the same, and to be issuing and payable out of the dividends, interest,`
  line `and annual income, of the said stocks, funds, and securities and to be paid and payable by equal`
  line `half-yearly payments on the thirtieth day of June and the thirty-first day of December; the first of the said`
  line `half-yearly payment to be made on the half-yearly day which shall first happen after the decease of the`
  line `person who shall have appointed such annuity or yearly sum, provided always, that in case any person on`
  line `whom such title shall descend, shall have refused or neglected to use the names of "Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy,"`
  line `or shall discontinue to use such names for six calendar months consecutively during his natural life, every`
  line `such limitation and appointment, either previously or afterwards made by him, shall be and become`
  line `inoperative and invalid; and no such annuity thereby created or appointed shall take effect or be payable`
  line `or chargeable on the said stocks, funds, and securities, notwithstanding any such limitation or`
  line appointment.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (36424)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Limit of aggregate of jointure payable contemporaneously.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36424&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Provided always, that the said`
  line `dividends, interest and annual income of the said stocks, funds, and securities shall not, at one and the`
  line `same time, be subject to the payment of more than the yearly sum of rupees twenty thousand for, or in`
  line `respect of, and jointure or jointures which shall be made in pursuance of the power hereinbefore`
  line `contained, so that, if by virtue of or under the same power, the said dividends, interest and annual income`
  line `would, in case this present provision had not been inserted, be charged at any one time with a greater`
  line `yearly sum for jointures in the whole than the yearly sum of rupees twenty thousand, the yearly sum`
  line `which shall occasion such excess, or such part thereof as shall occasion the same, shall, during the time of`
  line `such excess, abate and not be payable.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (36425)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Mansion House and hereditaments not to be subject to joiuture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36425&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The said Mansion House`
  line `and hereditaments called Mazagon castle, with their rights, members and appurtenances, and any lands,`
  line `houses, buildings and tenements which may be purchased or erected under the powers conferred by`
  line `section 8, with their rights, members, and appurtenances, shall not be subject to dower of any Dowager`
  line `Lady Jejeebhoy, or of the present or any future wife of Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, Fifth Baronet, or of any`
  line `wife of any of the persons who may successively be entitled to the Baronetcy under the aforesaid`
  line `limitations, or to any other right, interest, or estate whatsoever which any Dowager Lady Jejeebhoy or any`
  line `such wife or wives as aforesaid may or might have or claim to have in the said Mansion House, lands,`
  line `buildings and hereditaments, under any custom or law of the Parsees, or otherwise howsoever.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (36426)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Alienation prohibited during the Baronetcy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36426&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `So long as the said title and dignity of Baronet`
  line `shall endure, and until there shall be a failure of the heirs male of the body of the First Baronet to whom`
  line `the said title and dignity of Baronet might descend, pursuant to the limitations of the said Letters Patent,`
  line `neither Sir Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, Fifth Baronet, nor any of the heirs male of the body of Sir Jamsetjee`
  line `Jejeebhoy, First Baronet, in whose favour trusts are hereinbefore declared of the dividends, and annual`
  line `income of the said stocks, funds, and securities, or to whom the said Mansion House and hereditaments`
  line `called Mazagon Castle and any lands, buildings or other hereditaments, which may be purchased or`
  line `erected under the powers conferred by section 8 shall stand limited under this Act, shall transfer, dispose`
  line `of, alien, convey, charge, or encumber the said stocks, funds and securities, or any part thereof, or the`
  line `dividends, interest, and annual income thereof, or of any part thereof, or the said Mansion House or`
  line `hereditaments, or any lands, buildings or other hereditaments, which may be purchased or erected under`
  line `the power conferred by section 8 or any part thereof, for any greater or larger estate, interest or time, than`
  line `during his natural life, and for such portion thereof only as he shall continue to use the names of`
  line `"Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy," nor shall have any power to discontinue or bar the estate of any person or persons`
  line `for whose benefit trusts are declared by this Act of the dividends, interest, and annual income of the said`
  line `stocks, funds, and securities or to or upon whom the said Mansion House and hereditaments, and any`
  line `lands, buildings and other hereditaments, which may be purchased or erected under the powers conferred by section 8, and the rents and profits thereof are, by this Act, limited to come or devolve in any manner`
  line `whatsoever, either by default or otherwise, or to prevent any such person or persons from succeeding to,`
  line `holding, or enjoying, receiving or taking, the same premises, according to the true intent of the provisions`
  line `hereinbefore contained; nor shall the same premises, or any of them, be held, by any Court of Law or`
  line `Equity, to have vested in any such person as aforesaid for any greater estate or interest than during his`
  line `life, and only during such portion thereof as he shall continue to use the names of "Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy,"`
  line `and every attempt to make any conveyance, assignment, or assurance contrary to the intention of this Act`
  line `shall be, and is hereby declared and enacted to be, void.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (36442)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to augment the funds and securities subject to the Settlement, provided that total amount of funds su bject to the Settlement shall not exceed fifty lakh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36442&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `If at any time or times`
  line `hereafter the said Sir Power to Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, Fifth Baronet, or any other person or persons shall be`
  line `desirous of augmenting the funds and securities for the time being subject to the trusts of this Act, and for`
  line `that purpose and with that intent shall at his or her oven expense transfer and deliver to the Corporation`
  line `any stocks, funds, or securities of the kinds specified in section 6, then and as often as the same shall`
  line `happen the Corporation may, with the previous consent of the Governor of Bombay in Council, accept`
  line `such stocks, funds and securities, and the same shall thenceforth be held by the Corporation upon the`
  line `same trusts as those which are declared by this Act of and concerning the trust funds which are the subject`
  line `of the Settlement effected by this Act, or upon such of them as shall be then subsisting and capable of`
  line `taking effect:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total amount of the corpus of the trust funds which shall be subject to the trusts of`
  line `the Settlement effected by this Act shall at no time exceed fifty lakhs of rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (36443)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Provision as to insurances of Mazagon Castle, and other house or buildings purchased in lieu thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36443&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The person for the time being entitled to, and in the enjoyment of, the title of Baronet shall`
  line `at his own expense, insure the said Mansion House and other hereditaments, called Mazagon Castle, and`
  line `all buildings and offices accessory thereto, until such time as the same may be sold and the proceeds of`
  line `sale thereof paid to the Corporation, in the name to the Corporation against loss or damage by fire, in such`
  line `sum as the Corporation may deem adequate, and shall also, at his own expense, insure all houses and`
  line `other buildings, which may be purchased or erected under the powers conferred by section 8, from the`
  line `time when the same shall be conveyed to and become vested in the Corporation, against loss or damage`
  line `by fire, in such sum as the Corporation may deem adequate, and in case any such person shall at any time`
  line `neglect or refuse to insure the same in such amount or amounts, it shall be lawful for the Corporation to`
  line `insure the same and to apply any portion of the income of the funds for the time being subject to the trusts`
  line `of the Settlement effected by this Act to that purpose, and in case the hereditaments and premises so`
  line `insured or any part thereof shall be destroyed or damaged by fire, the moneys received in respect of such`
  line `insurance shall either be laid out under the directions of the Corporation in re-building or re-installing the`
  line `hereditaments and premises so destroyed or damaged by fire, or, upon the application of the person for`
  line `the time being entitled to, and in the enjoyment of, the said dignity of Baronet, and with the consent of the`
  line `Governor of Bombay in Council to be notified by a resolution of the Government of Bombay, may be laid`
  line `out in the purchase of other hereditaments in the Island of Bombay suitable for the support of the dignity`
  line `of the said Baronetcy and, in such last mentioned case, the hereditaments so purchased shall be conveyed`
  line `to and vested in the Corporation, and the Corporation shall hold the same upon the same trusts and for the`
  line `same ends, intents, and purposes, and with the same powers, as are declared and conferred by this Act of`
  line `and concerning the hereditaments and premises which shall have been so destroyed or damaged by fire as`
  line `aforesaid, or such of them as shall then be subsisting and capable of taking effect; and until such`
  line `insurance moneys shall have been so laid out as aforesaid, the Corporation may invest the same or any`
  line `part thereof in any of the securities specified in section 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (36444)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Directions for keeping Mazagone Castle, and other houses or buildings purchased in lieu thereof, in repair.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36444&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The person for the time being entitled to, and in the enjoyment of, the title of`
  line `Baronet conferred by the said letters Patent shall, at his own expense, keep in good repair, orders, and`
  line `condition, the said Mansion House and other hereditaments called Mazagon Castle and all offices and out`
  line `buildings accessory thereto, and likewise all houses and other buildings which may be purchased or`
  line `erected under the powers conferred by section 8, and all alterations and additions thereto, and all offices,`
  line `out-houses and other buildings accessory thereto, and, in case any person shall at any time neglect or refuse to keep the same or any part thereof in such good order and condition, it shall be lawful for the`
  line `Corporation to cause the same to be kept in good order and condition, and to defray the expenses`
  line `incidental thereto, out of the income of the funds for the time being subject to the trusts of the Settlement`
  line `effected by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (36430)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to Trustees to sell land subject to Settlement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36430&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation shall have power at any`
  line `time, with the consent of the person entitled to, and in the enjoyment of, the title of Baronet conferred by`
  line `the said Letters Patent, and of the Governor of Bombay in Council to be notified by a resolution of the`
  line `Government of Bombay to sell or exchange for other lands or hereditaments in the Island of Bombay any`
  line `lands or hereditaments which are subject to the trusts of the Settlement effected by this Act or any part`
  line `thereof, and upon any such exchange, to give or receive any money for equality of exchange:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Corporation shall not sell the Mansion House, if any, or the buildings accessory`
  line `thereto, which may be purchased, or erected under the powers conferred by this Act, without having first`
  line `consulted all persons who may be interested in the said Mansion House, either by way of reversion, or`
  line `otherwise, and who may have attained their respective ages of majority:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the foregoing proviso shall apply to the said Mansion House, and the buildings`
  line `accessory thereto only, and shall not apply to any lands, hereditaments, or premises, other than the land`
  line `upon which the said Mansion House and the buildings accessory thereto, may stand, or be erected, which`
  line `may be purchased under the powers conferred by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (36431)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Directions as to how sale may be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36431&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Any sale which may be effected under the powers`
  line `conferred by section 24 may be made either by public auction or private contract, and the Corporation`
  line `may make any stipulations as to title, or evidence, or commencement of title, or otherwise, in any`
  line `conditions of sale or contract for sale or exchange, of the said hereditaments or any part thereof, and may`
  line `buy in, or rescind, or vary any contract for sale or exchange, and re-sell, or re-exchange, without being`
  line `responsible for any loss occasioned thereby.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (36432)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Direction as investment of proceeds of sale of lands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36432&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation shall, with all`
  line `convenient speed, invest all moneys which may be received by them upon any sale or exchange which`
  line `shall be effected by them under the powers conferred by section 24, either in the purchase of any one or`
  line `more of the securities specified in section 6, or in the purchase of other lands and hereditaments in the`
  line `Island of Bombay, suitable for the support of the dignity of the said title; provided that every such`
  line `purchase of lands or hereditaments be made with the consent in writing of the person for the time being`
  line `entitled to, and in the enjoyment of, and said title conferred by the said Letters Patent.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (36433)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Declaration of Trusts as to investments of proceeds of sale of lands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36433&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation shall`
  line `hold all stocks, funds, and securities which may be purchased by them in pursuance of the directions`
  line `contained in section 26 upon the same trusts, and to the same ends, intents, and purposes, and with the`
  line `same powers as are by this Act declared of and concerning the trust funds of the Settlement effected by`
  line `this Act, and shall hold all lands and hereditaments may be purchased by them in pursuance of the`
  line `directions contained in section 26 upon the same trusts and to the same ends, intents, and purposes, and`
  line `with the same powers and are declared by this Act of and concerning all lands and hereditaments which`
  line `may be purchased under the powers conferred by section 8.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (36445)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to Baronet for the time being to enter into arrangement with Government as to land - revenue payable in respect of land purchased under section 8`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36445&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The person for the time being entitled`
  line `to, and in the enjoyment of, the title of Baronet conferred by the said Letters Patent as aforesaid, shall`
  line `have power with a view to the more advantageous sale of the land occupied by the said Mansion House`
  line `and other hereditaments, called Mazagon Castle, in other hereditaments, called Mazagon Castle, in`
  line `pursuance of the powers in that behalf conferred by section 10, and, notwithstanding anything in this Act`
  line `contained to the contrary, to enter into an arrangement with the Government of Bombay whereby, in`
  line `consideration of the waiver in perpetuity by the Government of Bombay of their right to enhance the`
  line `amount of the assessment to land revenue for the time being payable in respect of the land occupied by`
  line `the said Mansion House and other hereditaments, called Mazagon Castle, either the amount of the`
  line `assessment to land-revenue payable in respect of any land which may be purchased in pursuance of the`
  line `power in that behalf conferred by section 8, may be enhanced, or an assessment to land-revenue of any land so purchased, which at the time of the purchase thereof shall not be liable to the payment of`
  line `land-revenue, may be imposed thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (36435)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Indemnity of Trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36435&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The Trustees for the time being action in the execution of the trusts and`
  line `powers hereby created and reposed in them respectively, and their successors, respectively, shall be`
  line `changed and chargeable for such moneys only as he and they respectively shall actually receive by virtue`
  line `of the trusts, powers and provisions of this Act, notwithstanding his, their, or any of their giving or`
  line `signing, or joining in giving or singing any receipt or receipts, for the sake of conformity; and he and they`
  line `respectively shall not be answerable or accountable for any banker or broker, agent, or other person with`
  line `whom or in whose hands any part of the said trust moneys shall or may be deposited or lodged for safe`
  line `custody, or otherwise in the execution of any of the trusts, powers and provisions hereinbefore created or`
  line `contained; and the Trustees for the time being acting in the execution of the trusts and powers hereby`
  line `created, and reposed in them respectively, and their successors respectively, shall not be answerable or`
  line `accountable for the insufficiency or deficiency of any security or securities, stocks or funds, in or upon`
  line `which the said trust moneys or any part thereof shall be placed out or invested, nor for any other`
  line `misfortune, loss or damage which may happen in the execution of the aforesaid trusts, powers and`
  line `provisions or in relation thereto; and it shall be lawful for him and them respectively with or out of the`
  line `money which shall come to his or their respective hands by virtue of the trusts and provisions of this Act,`
  line `to retain and reimburse to himself and themselves respectively all costs, damages and expenses which he`
  line `and they respectively shall or may sustain, expend, or disburse in or about the execution of the aforesaid`
  line `powers, trusts, and provisions or in relation thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (36436)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `General saving clause.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "the King's Most Excellent Majesty, His heirs and successors".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455&sectionId=36436&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00019_191510_1523342223455
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Saving always ^1`
  line `[the Government], and to all and every other person and`
  line `persons, bodies politic and corporate, and his, her and their respective heirs, successors executors, and`
  line `administrators and every of them (other than and except the devisees, heirs and assigns of the said Sir`
  line `Jamsetjee Jejeebhoy, First Baronet), all such estate, right, title, interest, claim, and demand whatsoever of,`
  line `in, to, out of, or upon the said Mansion House and hereditaments, called Mazagon Castle, and any lands,`
  line `buildings or other hereditaments, which may be purchased or erected, under the powers conferred by`
  line `section 8 or any parts thereof, as they, every, or any of them had before the passing of this Act and`
  line `would, could, or might have had, held, or enjoyed in case this Act had not been passed.`
